    <item>
      <title>Ecosystem services in urban landscapes</title>
      <link>https://xp-song.github.io/project/ess_external/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Jan 2016 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://xp-song.github.io/project/ess_external/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Urban vegetation and green spaces provide cities with a number of benefits which are known as ‘ecosystem services’. These include reducing flood risk, cooling urban areas, and providing spaces for recreation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most research on urban ecosystem services has been conducted in temperate Europe and North America, but we know relatively little about how tropical urban areas can be designed to enhance ecosystem service provision. Tropical areas, particularly Southeast Asia, are rapidly becoming more urban, with cities growing larger and people living in higher densities. It is therefore important to better understand how urban greenery can contribute to enhancing the sustainability of such cities.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The main aim of this project is to use new types of data and modelling approaches to improve urban landscape design and obtain the greatest value from ecosystem services. Physical, ecological and socio-cultural parameters are used as inputs to model various types of ecosystem services. The landscape is designed using 3D point cloud data, which produces a representation of the landscape that is highly accurate. The iterative process of model simulation and design feedback provides opportunities to improve designs based on scientific results.&lt;/p&gt;

